│ `PreserveLCSSA` is true and there are loop exits.                           │
│                                                                             │
│ Then `UpdatePHINodes` is called with `HasLoopExit = true`, which means it   │
│ won't try to optimize away PHI nodes.                                       │
│                                                                             │
│ But this still only handles existing PHI nodes, not new LCSSA phis for      │
│ non-PHI instructions.                                                       │
│                                                                             │
│ The real LCSSA formation should happen after all block splitting is         │
│ complete.                                                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ In `formDedicatedExitBlocks`, after all blocks are split, it should call    │
│ `formLCSSA` to create LCSSA phis in the final block structure.              │
│                                                                             │
│ Let me check if `formDedicatedExitBlocks` does this.                        │
│                                                                             │
│ Looking at the implementation in LoopUtils.cpp:                             │
│                                                                             │
│ ```cpp                                                                      │
